    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\ni prefer using actual tabs in my code instead of using `expandtab` for spaces. when using spaces, the `listchars` option offers a very nice `leadmultispace` value, which is useful to mimick indentation guides (`vim.opt.listchars = 'leadmultispace:▏ '`)\n\nif i were to use just `multispace`, then id get indentation guides in the middle of lines too, which looks awkward when i just want to align properties, for example\n\nthe same `lead`-value doesnt exist for tabs, so im stuck with `listchars = 'tab:▏ '` and the issue described in the above paragraph\n\n<img width=\"723\" height=\"294\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/21611551-8fd2-48d8-9b9c-3c30bb218b8e\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ni think a `leadtab` value for the `listchars` option that applies the listchars only at the beginning of lines up until the first 'significant' character would be cool",
